        "solution": "1. Identify the values: $n = 4$, $a_1 = 10$, and $d = 5$.\n2. Use the sum formula: $S_n = \\frac{n}{2}[2a_1 + (n-1)d]$.\n3. Substitute the values: $S_4 = \\frac{4}{2}[2(10) + (4 - 1)5]$.\n4. Simplify: $S_4 = 2[20 + 3(5)] = 2[20 + 15] = 2[35] = 70$.\nTherefore, the sum of the first 4 terms is 70.",
